      "id": 1,
      "text": "In the 1960s Michigan businessman Harold Schwartz began selling land that would become The Villages through mail‑order sales.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Villages%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1992 the community officially adopted the name \"The Villages\".",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Villages%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "By the early 1990s The Villages had grown to over 8,000 residents, three golf courses, and a Winn‑Dixie supermarket.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        24
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Villages%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Between 2010 and 2019 The Villages was the top‑selling master‑planned community in the United States, moving 24,440 homes.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        25
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Villages%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Fictitious historical markers and architectural details create an atmosphere that feels like an idyllic 1800s small town.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Villages%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "The community sits about 55 miles northwest of Orlando and 80 miles northeast of Tampa, near Wildwood, Lady Lake, and Fruitland Park.",
